#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:22
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Info is a type of documentation. The documents are in a file format called "
"texinfo, and can be read on the command line with the <ulink url=\"info:/info"
"\"><command>info</command></ulink> program."
msgstr ""
"ni A Ubwoko: Bya Inyandiko . Inyandiko in A Idosiye Imiterere , na Soma ku i "
"command Umurongo: Na: i <command> Ibisobanuro </command> Porogaramu . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:26
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Info KIO worker allows you to read the info pages installed on your "
"system, from within &konqueror;. You can use it very easily:"
msgstr ""
"Kuri Soma i Ibisobanuro Amapaji yakorewe iyinjizaporogaramu ku Sisitemu , "
"Kuva: muri &konqueror; . Koresha : "

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:29
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>info:</command><replaceable>gcc</replaceable></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput> <command> Ibisobanuro : </command> <replaceable> </replaceable> "
"</userinput> "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:31
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This would show you the top level node of the Info documentation for the "
"&gcc; compiler."
msgstr ""
"Herekana %S i Hejuru: urwego Bya i Inyandiko ya:  i &gcc; Rukusanya: . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:34
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Info is a &GNU; replacement for <command>man</command>, but is not widely "
"used outside of &GNU; software."
msgstr ""
"ni A &GNU; ya:  <command> </command> , ni OYA Byakoreshejwe Hanze Bya "
"&GNU; . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:38
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can quite easily browse the info documentation you have installed from "
"within the &khelpcenter; application, or you can use the info KIO worker "
"directly from within both &konqueror; and the mini-cli."
msgstr ""
"Gushakisha i Ibisobanuro Inyandiko yakorewe iyinjizaporogaramu Kuva: muri i "
"&khelpcenter; Porogaramu , Cyangwa Koresha i Ibisobanuro Kuva: muri Byombi "
"&konqueror; na i - . "
